input: Type: Song, Theme: A hero's return, Style: Shakespearean
output:
Upon thy return, my noble steed,
Thou hast completed thy quest with valorous deed.
The foe hath been vanquished, and peace restored in sight.
Thy valor and courage shall be eternally remembered, no doubt.

Thou art a hero, without a doubt,
Whose feats of valor, shall forever be brought to our court.
We greet thee with open arms, thy heart full of joy and pride.
Thou art welcome here, in honor and in thy stride.

So raise your jolly huzza, and give us cheer,
As we celebrate thy return from afar.
For thou hast brought honor to thyself, thy country, and thy name.
Thou art truly a hero, whose deeds will forever remain.
